<plot>Vera Vague, in this Columbia All-Star Comedy (production number 7423), is strongly against fibbing in any fashion, and gives her maid a stern lecture when she catches her doing so. Complications and circumstances soon put Vera in a position of having to tell several fibs in order to pull herself out of a mess with her boss and her boy friend. The maid is a bemused-and-confused observer.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?091277</url></doc>
